Charlton Athletic boss Lee Bowyer wants youngsters Alfie Doughty and Albie Morgan to exit the Valley on loan deals in a bid to gain more first-team experience. The pair both started last night’s Carabao Cup first round clash with Forest Green Rovers, as the Addicks suffered a surprise exit via a penalty shoot-out. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network But whilst Bowyer described Doughty as the best of the Addicks’ young players on the pitch last night, the Charlton boss, according to South London Press , is not ruling out the possibility of them exiting the club on loan before the window shuts.